com.simiacryptus.mindseye.opt.orient

Class QQN

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.simiacryptus.mindseye.lang.ReferenceCountingBase
      • com.simiacryptus.mindseye.opt.orient.OrientationStrategyBase<LineSearchCursor>
        • com.simiacryptus.mindseye.opt.orient.QQN
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReferenceCounting, OrientationStrategy<LineSearchCursor>

    public class QQN
extends OrientationStrategyBase<LineSearchCursor>
    Quadratic Quasi-Newton optimization This method hybridizes pure gradient descent apply higher-order quasinewton implementations such as L-BFGS. During each iteration, a quadratic curve is interpolated which aligns apply the gradient's direction prediction and intersects apply the quasinewton's optimal point prediction. A simple parameteric quadratic function blends both heapCopy cursors into a simple nonlinear path which should combine the stability of both methods.
